Measurement Units in CSS
-width
-Height
-Margin
-Padding, etc

In general CSS SUPPORT TWO KIND OF UNITS

1. Absolute Unit - They are fixed United , for example if you assign Property like 200px it means you need to have this measurement
                   no matter what
   Example: Pixel(px), Centimeter (cm), Millimeter(mm), Inch(in), Points(pt), Pica(pc)

   1px = 1/96th of 1in
   1in = 2.54cm


2. Relative Unit - This specifies length relative to another property. It means that relative units scaled better between different rendering mediums

(rem,em,vw,vh,%)
